
SCILS News and Events: NJ ASIS&T Distinguished Lectureship; Professor Christine L. Borgman to present 'Digital Libraries, Past, Present and Future'
Professor Christine Borgman will present her research in a talk entitled
"Digital Libraries: Past, Present, and Future"
"Digital Libraries -- Recent Research"
NJ/ASIS&T Distinguished Lectureship Award presentation, followed by an address by Professor Christine Borgman:
Abstract: The talk will provide an overview of digital libraries, including the competing definitions of the term, and address how they developed, discuss current issues of research and practice, and highlight emerging issues and trends. Background reading: "From Gutenberg to the Global Information Infrastructure: Access to Information in the Networked World." by Christine L. Borgman. MIT Press, 2000 (or paperback edition, 2003).